author: Brian
title: Big-time celebrities take over the Daytona 500

persons.name: mark j. rebilas mark j. rebilas-usa

text:
Feb 26, 2017 at 11:04a ET 0Shares 
The stars are out for the 59 th running of the Daytona 500, with live coverage on FOX beginning at 1 p.m. ET and a green flag time of 2:20 p.m. 
Here are some of the stars in attendance today at the World Center of Racing. Mark J. Rebilas Mark J. Rebilas-USA TODAY Sports Jordan Sparks The National Anthem will be performed by Sparks, who is well known for her run on “American Idol” and films “Sparkle,” “Dear Secret Santa” and the upcoming “God Bless the Broken Road.” Sparks was a presenter at 2016 NASCAR Sprint Cup Awards. Getty Images Ethan Miller Guy Fieri Fieri is an American restaurateur, author, game show host, and television personality. He co-owns six restaurants in California and is known for his television series on the Food Network. NASCAR NASCAR via Getty Images Ladanian Tomlinson A former NFL running back who spent most of his career with the San Diego Chargers, Tomlinson is a five-time Pro Bowler, six- time All- Pro and won two FL rushing titles in 2006-07. Keanu Reeves 
One of Hollywood’s top stars, Reeves’ body of work includes the films “Speed,” “The Matrix,” “John Wick”, “Point Break,” “Devil’s Advocate,” “Hard Ball” and “Bill & Ted’s Excellent Adventure.” Anthony “Rumble” Johnson The No. 1 Light Heavyweight in the UFC, Johnson has five sub-one-minute KO wins, the most in UFC history. Zuffa LLC via Getty Images Josh Hedges/Zuffa LLC Laurie Hernandez A member of the Fab Five Olympic Gymnastics team, Hernandez was a Gold & Silver medalist at the 2016 Rio Olympics and a winner of “Dancing with the Stars” last year. Geoff Burke-USA TODAY Sports Geoff Burke Lady Antebellum 
The 2011 Grammy Award winners for Song of the Year will perform the pre-race concert. The group also won the 2010 Grammy for Best Country Performance by Duo or Group with Vocals, CMA’s 2009 Vocal Group of the Year and in 2010 became the first artist in CMA history to win Single of the Year for two consecutive years. Mario Andretti 
The 1967 Daytona 500 champion is the honorary race official for the 59th annual Daytona 500. Rob Gronkowski 
The two-time Super Bowl-winning tight end for the New England Patriots is taking in NASCAR's biggest race. WPPROD
